text: What is the difference between Android and Android one?
What is an Android One phone?
What is so special about Android one?

Android One is a near-stock version of the Android operating system released by Google. Android One cannot be altered by the companies that make the phones, and only runs on certain smartphones. The Android One brand promises regular security updates for three years, and Android OS updates for two years.
